ertificateBuilder, X509Bundle, and RevocationServer flows using RSA/EC/EdDSA keys. Guard or avoid synthetic ML-DSA-specific tests on JDKs where java.security.AsymmetricKey is unavailable; that failure is a JDK-version-sensitive code path, not missing setup.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported failure comes from the ML-DSA preferredSignatureAlgorithm path trying to reflectively load java.security.AsymmetricKey; extra Maven dependencies cannot provide that JDK class.\",\n    \"RevocationServer binds a random localhost port using jdk.httpserver; this should not need Docker, but tests covering CRLs depend on loopback networking being available.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03e5d349d0658496016a3e9d7d2d548197a069cd6dbe65c6c9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 9556, "output": 763, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42063, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782488430197, "responseId": "resp_03e5d349d0658496016a3e9d6eaa5c81978bd4be404d52a3f7"}}
